er making a flashy debut on the Philadelphia stage.   Illustrated with scores of rare archival images, Insight Philadelphia will give readers a new appreciation for the people and places that make the City of Brotherly Love so unique.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 4aAzavea. 4aPennsylvania. 4aPhiladelphia. 4aPhilly. 4aguide. 4ahistory. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066330308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017-2018z978311065742508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018z978311066608340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813597478423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813597478.jpg  a978-3-11-065742-5  RUP eBook-Package 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066330-3  RUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-066608-3  RUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG